The paper deals with multimedia forensics, which involves analyzing visual content such as images and videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the second likely category. The paper also deals with identifying the source of digital media, which involves cryptography and security, suggesting cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the third likely category. The paper also involves searching and comparing visual content, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the fifth likely category.
